Looking at the `getCurrentPublishDateAsCalendar` function:

```kotlin
private fun getCurrentPublishDateAsCalendar(postRepository: EditPostRepository): Calendar {
    val calendar = localeManagerWrapper.getCurrentCalendar()
    val dateCreated = postRepository.dateCreated  // This line can cause NPE
    // Set the currently selected time if available
    if (!TextUtils.isEmpty(dateCreated)) {
        calendar.time = DateTimeUtils.dateFromIso8601(dateCreated)
        calendar.timeZone = localeManagerWrapper.getTimeZone()
    }
    return calendar
}
```

The fix should be to check `hasPost()` before accessing `dateCreated`, or use `getPost()?.dateCreated` to safely access the dateCreated property.

Since `getPost()` returns `PostImmutableModel?`, we can use it to safely access the dateCreated. Let me look at what the PostImmutableModel has.

